# Reflect Tables into SQLAlchemy ORM


```python
# Python SQL toolkit and Object Relational Mapper
import sqlalchemy
from sqlalchemy.ext.automap import automap_base
from sqlalchemy.orm import Session
from sqlalchemy import create_engine, func
from datetime import datetime, timedelta
```


```python
engine = create_engine("sqlite:///Resources/hawaii.sqlite")
```


```python
# reflect an existing database into a new model
Base = automap_base()
# reflect the tables
Base.prepare(engine, reflect=True)
```


```python
# We can view all of the classes that automap found
Base.classes.keys()
```




    ['measurement', 'station']




```python
# Save references to each table
Measurement = Base.classes.measurement
Station = Base.classes.station
```


```python
# Create our session (link) from Python to the DB
precip = engine.execute("SELECT date, prcp FROM measurement ;")
cols, data = precip.keys(), precip.fetchall() 
```

# Exploratory Climate Analysis


```python
# Calculate the date 1 year ago from today
N = 365

date_N_days_ago = datetime.now() - timedelta(days=N)

print(date_N_days_ago)
```

    2017-08-06 19:36:55.714122
    


```python
pd.DataFrame(data, columns=cols).head() # Pass into the dataframe constructor
weather_df = pd.DataFrame(data, columns=cols)
weather_py = weather_df[weather_df['date'] > date_N_days_ago]
weather_py.head
grouped_weather = weather_py.groupby(['date'],as_index=False).sum()
```


```python
# Design a query to retrieve the last 12 months of precipitation data and plot the results
plt.plot
```

```python
# Write a function called `calc_temps` that will accept start date and end date in the format '%Y-%m-%d' 
# and return the minimum, average, and maximum temperatures for that range of dates
Start_date = '2017-06-30'
End_date = '2017-07-31'

between_dates = comb_data[(comb_data['date'] > Start_date) & (comb_data['date'] > End_date)]
```


```python
#Average, Min and Max temp for the selected dates
print("Min:",between_dates.tobs.agg(np.min),"Max:",between_dates.tobs.agg(np.max),"Ave:",between_dates.tobs.agg(np.mean))
```

    Min: 70.0 Max: 85.0 Ave: 78.82417582417582
    


```python
Tmean=between_dates.tobs.agg(np.mean)
Tmax=between_dates.tobs.agg(np.max)
Tmin=between_dates.tobs.agg(np.min)

data = {'Tmin':Tmin,'Tmax':Tmax,'Tmean':Tmean}

wdata=pd.DataFrame.from_dict(data, orient='index')
wdata = wdata.transpose()
```


```python
# Plot the results from your previous query as a bar chart. 
# Use "Trip Avg Temp" as your Title
# Use the average temperature for the y value
# Use the peak-to-peak (tmax-tmin) value as the y error bar (yerr
n_groups = 1
means_t = wdata.Tmean
std_t = wdata.Tmean - wdata.Tmax

fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(6, 4))
index = np.arange(n_groups)
bar_width = .001
opacity = 0.4
error_config = {'ecolor': '0.3'}

rects1 = ax.bar( index, means_t, bar_width,
                alpha=opacity, color='coral',
                yerr=std_t, error_kw=error_config,
                label='Average Temp')

ax.set_ylabel('Temp (F)')
ax.set_title('Trip Avg Temp')
ax.set_xticks(index )
ax.legend()
fig.tight_layout()
plt.show()
```
